FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - NEPAL: (GANDAKI) LIVESTOCK, SEROTYPE ASIA 1, OIE
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 9 Feb 2018
Source: Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(07) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=25917


Foot-and-mouth disease, Nepal
-----------------------------
Information received on 9 Feb 2018 from Dr Bimal Kumar Nirmal, Department of Livestock Services, Ministry of Livestock Development, Nepal

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 9 Dec 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 8 Feb 2018
Report date: 9 Feb 2018
Date event resolved: 23 Jan 2018
Reason for notification: Recurrence of listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2013
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: Asia 1
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Phalepatan, Kaski, Gandaki
Date of start of the outbreak: 9 Dec 2017
Outbreak status: resolved on 23 Jan 2018
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 15 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Buffaloes / 7 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Lactating cattle and buffaloes were affected with symptoms like ropy salivation, lacrimation, anorexia, lameness and fever.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 20 / 0 / 0 / 0
Buffaloes / 14.29 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Introduction of new live animals
Epidemiological comments: The buffaloes and milking cows were purchased from traders who used to collect animals from various parts of the bordering district of the neighboring country.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, quarantine, disinfection, no treatment of affected animals,

Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
Gandaki / Buffaloes / 50 / 1 km around the farm
[Gandaki] / Cattle / 100 / 1 km around the farm
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Foot and Mouth Disease and Transboundary Animal Diseases Laboratory, Budanilakantha (National laboratory) / Cattle / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 25 Dec 2017 / Positive
Foot and Mouth Disease and Transboundary Animal Diseases Laboratory, Budanilakantha (National laboratory) / Cattle/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 Dec 2017 / Positive
Pirbright Institute, United Kingdom (OIE reference laboratory) / Cattle / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 8 Feb 2018 / Positive
Pirbright Institute, United Kingdom (OIE reference laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction / 8 Feb 2018 / Positive
Pirbright Institute, United Kingdom (OIE reference laboratory) / Cattle / serotyping / 8 Feb 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the current report, it was indicated that 2013 was the last year of occurrence for serotype Asia 1. The OIE 2013 annual report from Nepal shows the country as having had 66 outbreaks involving FMD serotypes O and Asia 1. The report can be accessed at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/semestrial/review?year=2013&semester=0&wild=0&country=NPL&this_country_code=NPL&detailed=1.

During the 1st semester of 2017, Nepal reported 45 outbreaks of FMD serotypes O and A. See report at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/semestrial/review?year=2017&semester=1&wild=0&country=NPL&this_country_code=NPL&detailed=1.

In addition, in August 2017, Nepal also reported a new strain involving FMD serotype A (A/ASIA/G-VII lineage); see posting 20170824.5271563. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Kaski, Western Region, Nepal: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5624306,34750]
